Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with video summarization, which is a subfield of computer vision. The proposed method, FrameRank, uses frame-to-frame level affinity graph to identify coherent and informative frames to summarize a video. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with video summarization, which is a subfield of multimedia. The proposed dataset, UGSum52, is a user-generated video summarization dataset that consists of 52 videos. 
3. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper proposes an unsupervised video summarization method that employs a frame-to-frame level affinity graph to identify coherent and informative frames to summarize a video. This can be seen as a form of information retrieval from videos. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper proposes a method that uses text processing techniques such as Kullback-Leibler(KL)-divergence-based graph to rank temporal segments according to the amount of semantic information contained in their frames. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The proposed method, FrameRank, is an unsupervised video summarization method that uses a frame-to-frame level affinity graph to identify coherent and informative frames to summarize a video. This can be seen as a form of machine learning.
